Rice transplanters are mainly classified based on their type and operation. In terms of type, they are categorized into Riding Type and Walking Type. Riding type transplanters are more advanced and offer greater efficiency compared to walking type, making them popular among farmers with large rice fields. When considering operation, rice transplanters can be manual, mechanical, or hydraulic. Manual transplanters are simple and require physical effort, while mechanical and hydraulic transplanters are automated and provide higher precision and productivity. Geographically, the market is segmented into North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, and the Middle East and Africa. Asia-Pacific dominates the global rice transplanter market due to the high cultivation of rice in countries like India, China, and Japan.

